4ï¸âƒ£ Why Elixir needs the event (this answers your question directly)

Elixir does not need Rails.
It needs information about what happened.

Elixir wants to know:

Who?

What?

When?

With what data?

The event carries that context.

Example:

Rails says: â€œA notification was requested.â€

Elixir says: â€œOkay, Iâ€™ll send it asynchronously.â€

